# Code of Conduct

We wish for people on IndieWeb to have a safe time. As such, we ask you follow this code of conduct.

## Be Nice.
Everyone has a background behind their github account, a real person. So keep in mind that
people mentioned in or using your website can experience feelings, like being hurt. So
please be considerate.

## Be Honest.
Don't spread misinformation, rumours, or lies across IndieWeb, we want you to come
as you are. However, you are asked to use an alias for privacy.

## Keep confidential information secret.
Don't share your adress, email, passwords, or any information that could be used to Identify and/or
harm you. You are allowed to use your name, but you are strongly discouraged from doing so.

## Don't Swear.
We don't want swear words used here. If you use swear words in this community, we will likely
take action to stop you, either by declining pull requests or trying to put you on a blacklist.
If you would like to swear, please choose another community.

## Keep things PG.
Anything that's PG-13 or worse should be excluded from this website. We don't want innapropriate
content or mature TV stuff. If you wish to do PG-13 or higher, please choose another community.

## Follow all U.S. Laws.
Follow U.S. Laws when using this website, this is just in general. But I want to emphasize it,
even if you don't live in the U.S. If for whatever reason, you cannot follow these laws, please
choose another community.
